The '''Outer Rim Communications Center''' was located on [[Generis/Legends|Generis]] in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]] and was established by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]]. It was later used by the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]. The facility was commanded by [[Kryll|General Kryll]], a former [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] officer turned Rebel and staffed by the Atrivis Communications Group. It was centered at Generis's pole, near a [[hiridiu crystal]] deposit.

When Generis was attacked by [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]] in [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]], Kryll's forces were quickly overwhelmed. However, he and [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Pash Cracken]] were able to arrange the escape of [[Atrivis sector/Legends|Atrivis sector]] [[Commander-in-Chief/Legends|Commander-in-Chief]] [[Travia Chan/Legends|Travia Chan]] along with her staff.

The New Republic eventually recovered Generis, and the station back from the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. During the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], it served as one of the two stations the New Republic used to stay in contact with the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]]. The [[Yuuzhan Vong]] took advantage of this, destroying it. After this, [[Esfandia/Legends|Esfandia]] remained as the only planet to have contact with the Unknown Regions.<ref name="Force Heretic III">''[[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic III: Reunion]]''</ref>

